quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
  41,21,"And they say to their skins, “Why did you testify against us?” They say, “Allah, Who made everything speak, made us speak.” It is He Who created you<sup>pl </sup>the first time, and to Him you are returned{1}.",footnotes:1:[Qira’at: Ya’qub read it as: “…and to him you return.”]
  41,22,"And you<sup>pl </sup>were unable to hide yourselves in a way that neither your hearing nor your sight<i>(s) </i>nor your skins were prevented from testifying against you, and you thought that Allah does not know much of what you do."
  41,23,"And it is that thought of yours about your<sup>pl </sup>Lord that led you to ruin—so you became of the losers."
  41,24,"So even if they endure patiently, the Fire is<i>(still) </i>a dwelling for them; and if they ask to make amends, they will not be allowed to amend."
  41,25,"And We assigned for them comrades who then adorned for them what was before them and what was behind them, and the Word came to pass against them among communities of unseen beings{1}and humans that passed away before them; indeed, they were losers.",footnotes:1:[The Arabic word used is <i>jinn</i> which are unseen beings that are accountable for their actions.]
  41,26,"Those who denied said, “Do not listen to this recitation{1}and speak noisily during it so that you<sup>pl </sup>may overcome.”",footnotes:1:[The Arabic word used is Qur’anwhich literally means ‘recital’ or ‘recitation’.]
  41,27,"We will certainly make those who have denied taste a severe punishment, and We will certainly repay them for the worst of what they used to do."
  41,28,"Such is the repayment of Allah’s enemies—the Fire; therein for them is the Home of Eternity, a repayment on account of how theyused to repudiate Our signs."
  41,29,"And those who denied said, “Our Lord, show us those two<i>(groups) </i>which misguided us—among unseen beings<sup>a </sup>and humankind—so that we can trample them both under our feet so they become of the lowest.”",footnotes:1:[The Arabic word used is <i>jinn</i> which are unseen beings that are accountable for their actions.]
